Ben Ngubane Picture: Esa Alexander Public Enterprises Minister Lynne Brown has announced the resignation of Eskom chairman Ben Ngubane. Dr Ben Ngubane has resigned with immediate effect as non-executive director and chairperson of the board of Eskom, Brown said yesterday. Dr Ngubane formally tendered his resignation which I accepted. To ensure continuity at Eskom I have decided to appoint Mr Zethembe Khoza as interim chairperson until I am able to take new board appointments to cabinet for approval. Eskom s AGM is scheduled to take place later this month. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share